For 16x8 Quant, the default is to store the bias as 64 bit. However, 64 bit is 1.5~2 times slower than 32 bits so there is a feature request to enable 32 bit bias in 16x8 Quant. Users can test their model's accuracy and performance with both 32 bit and 64 bit and finalize which options to go by themselves. The default is {32bit for int8Quant, 64bit for int16Quant}.

Int32 bias for 16x8 Quant can be turned on by the below line:

converter._experimental_full_integer_quantization_bias_type = dtypes.int32
